pan><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/02 7:44:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Song:35. Bring weapon up? Or continue Song?</span><hr size=1> Hit lvl37 last night and brought BS up to 35.<br><br>The next level up in Song is Snare at spec 41, that's a costly investment with no return until 41.<br><br>So, question is;<br>Should I continue to invest in Song, at the cost of Weapon? Or halt BS now (for the time being) and bring weapon spec up?<br><br>My feeling is to halt BS and bring weapon up, but I wanted opinions from folks in case I'm missing something in my judgement.<br><br>Thx.<br><br>* Note: my final template is 46Song/44Weapon/17Parry <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kyus>kyus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/02 9:35:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Me too</span><hr size=1> I was wondering the same thing after coming out of the 3rd battlegrounds (where it is important to keep songs with level)  I decided to pump everything into hammer now until I get to the half dings in 40+.  I think it will improve leveling compared to songs.<br><br>I'm going for the 47 hammer / 46 song temp.<br><br>Kyus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/unamuna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namuna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/02 10:20:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Me too</span><hr size=1> Hmmmmm, 47Weapon/46Song. Hmmmm<br><br>- We're ALL about upfront dmg<br>- DD, DD, Swing, Mez and wait, then DD, DD, Swing again (anyone NOT doing this?)...More weapon spec good, more Parry does SQUAT<br>- 2h weapons HALVES the parry rate of the target. Since we all already have CRAP Parry, then this makes it even worse.<br><br>I'm thinkin more and more of changing my spec to this too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/02 11:16:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Me too</span><hr size=1> I would keep raising songs for one simple reason: the 46 damage add song. At higher levels, soloing becomes unreasonably slow and therefore grouping is a must. The damage song is the real reason groups want us so max it now to make your groups more effective. <br><br>I personally am going to solo with a buffbot to 50. At 42, I find it takes way too long to find a group and 75% if not more of them are nothing to write home about. It's sad when I get excited over guild chat about a group that is all my level rather than carrying a 35 or two along with it. I just can't take it anymore.<br><br>Because of this, I don't plan on getting the last damage song till 49 when I might group in order to get seals. My songs will remain at 35 till then. My final template will either be 46/46/10 or 46/47/5.<br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uharleybrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HarleyBrown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/02 5:02:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Me too</span><hr size=1> Namuna,<br><br>I had the same dilemna coming from 35 and realising that there were quite a few levels before you got anything from increasing BS.<br><br>I am now 42.  My BS is at 42.   However during the mid-late 30s I increased my hammer spec way more than my BS spec, and I think it wasnt until 39 that I restarted applying into BS.  That combined with the mini dings has allowed me to catch up on my level, and I really think the additional points into hammer helped my damage considerably - that and you get conquerer at 29. <p>Bragge Tunecrusher (Skald) <BR>Gunreth Doublebarrel (Berserker) <BR>Yelrah Mingunr (Hunter) <BR>Knights of Ni on Kay<BR>-------------------------------<BR>Ever dance with the devil in the moonlight?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uquiver6.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quiver6</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/24/02 10:10:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.noggy.org/dkbanner%20(1).jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 35 now... so what should I do</span><hr size=1> ok, from 35 to 41 there isn't really anything in the BS line.  So should I spec weapons up for the next 4 levels then start using my mini dings to get to my 46 song or keep songs at level and bring up weapon when I can.<br><br>Now that I'm posting this I'm thinking that I can go stright weapon to level 39 or 40 and catch up quickly.<br><br>BTW I'm going 46 songs, 44 weapon, 17 Parry <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uavelan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avelan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/27/02 12:30:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 35 now... so what should I do</span><hr size=1> This might be more with guild/alliance but I had to raise my sword up becuase I just cannot find a group.  I have a 41 skald and have 35 in song and sword, rest in parry.  I am definitely not as fast as skalds full song at 41 but I do more damage with sword. <br><br>Now with are shouts being resisted more, or so it seems, higher weap spec may be the key.<br><br>When respec comes out I might respec to hammer and bump song back to full and what I have left into hammer but haven't decided.<br><br> <p>Palomide Server<br>Dragonsong 41stNorse Skald<br>Cavedragon 39th Troll Shaman<br>Dragonblades 26th Troll Berserker<br>Dragonstorm 11th Norse Thane</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=198.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=198.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://p